Tround International Incsaid it entered into a joint agreement with &lt;Lucas AerospaceLtd>.    The company said the agreement calls for the selection ofcertain Tround products for use both with the Lucas 50 calibergun turret on helicopters and other vehicles and to establish asales effort for these products.    The two companies are negotiating with the U.S. Navy toflight-qualify the joint system, which will be adapted to ahelicopter provided by the Navy.    Tround said the system has the potential for revenues inexcess of 300 mln dlrs over a six-to-eight-year production timespan, assuming the project is a success. Reuter&#3;